{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "08", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "19", "M": "02", "S": "56"}}, "news": [{"title": "Citizens\u2019 group urges pause on NAKSHA land verification in Cuncolim", "para": "Citizens for Democracy Goa wants the government to pause property verification.  They demand formal guidelines and legal basis for the ongoing exercise.  Thousands of residents face anxiety due to the short 30-day deadline.  Many long-term residents lack complete historical documentation for their properties.  The group warns of legal uncertainty and potential chaos if the process continues.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/cuncolim-residents-face-uncertainty-as-citizens-group-demands-halt-to-naksha-land-verification/132259053?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-535774/132259053.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "PG rent rises across Chennai as food costs and LPG prices push up monthly expenses", "para": "Paying guest accommodation rents have significantly increased across Chennai and Tambaram. Operators have raised prices by at least thirty-five percent due to higher commercial LPG costs. Separate food charges have also been introduced, impacting student budgets. Many tenants now face higher monthly expenses for their shared living spaces. This situation is causing considerable financial strain for young professionals and students.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/rising-costs-of-pg-accommodation-in-chennai-rent-and-food-charges-skyrocket/132258962?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29813/132258962.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Second phase of NAKSHA begins in Panaji & Margao, owners told to submit title papers", "para": "The land records directorate has begun a pilot project for property ownership verification. Owners must appear before inquiry officers with title documents for verification. Boundaries were verified in the first phase, and now titles are being processed. Draft property cards will be prepared after inquiry, allowing for objections. This process aims to create digital title records with unique identification numbers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/naksha-project-launches-second-phase-in-panaji-and-margao-for-property-title-verification/132258995?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1439212/132258995.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}